Bien vu Arnaud, tu as raison — la cartographie des écrans faisait bien partie du point initial sur la mesure dans la slide DURABILITY. Voici la slide 1 corrigée, avec la cartographie réintégrée dans la section “Data-driven Lifecycle Management”, en anglais comme demandé :

⸻

Slide 1 – DURABILITY

📌 Optimizing Device Lifecycle
	•	Gradual shift from CAPEX to a hybrid OPEX/leasing model (via 3Step-IT & Leasing Solutions)
	•	Goal: balance performance, cost control, and sustainability

📌 Adapting to AI-related Needs
	•	With the rise of AI/NPU workloads, some user profiles require shorter refresh cycles
	•	Allocation policy is evolving to better match devices with real usage needs

📌 Data-driven Lifecycle Management
	•	Global screen mapping system deployed to identify and track all monitors by country and entity
	•	Average PC age increased from 2.9 to 3.5 years, average monitor age is 6 years
	•	Enhanced laptop instrumentation (CPU, memory, boot time…) to define optimal replacement timing

📌 Responsible End-of-Life
	•	Current partnerships with eco-organisms
	•	New deal in preparation with 3Step-IT to develop structured reuse and recycling programs
	•	Visit conducted with P&P recycling facility to explore operational integration

